{
  "_doc": "Extraction manifest for the Fable design references. The two source HTML files in references/ are the PRESERVED ORIGINALS (never edit/delete). This manifest drives breaking each component out into a GENERIC, variable-driven standalone snippet under components/. Each entry lists the variables that must replace the hardcoded (spray-foam) demo content so the component drops into ANY brand. Status: 'pending' = not yet extracted, 'done' = generic snippet exists. Safe to batch-process (e.g. delegate extraction to a cheaper LLM) one entry at a time.",
  "convention": {
    "accents": "Colors become CSS custom properties as space-separated RGB triplets (e.g. --accent: 168 85 247) so rgb(var(--accent) / <alpha>) builds any tint. One property re-themes the whole component.",
    "content": "Client-specific text/numbers become {{HANDLEBARS}} placeholders (e.g. {{PHONE}}, {{RATE_PER_UNIT}}, {{HEADLINE}}). NO FoamOps / spray-foam / R-40 strings survive in a generic component.",
    "file": "components/<slug>.html \u2014 self-contained: scoped CSS + minimal JS, a :root var block at top listing every knob, and a leading comment documenting variables + the conversion-rule note where relevant.",
    "reduced_motion": "Always keep the @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) guard."
  },
